  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "When a Ceph daemon crashes, it writes a report to ``/var/lib/ceph/crash/$uniqueid/``.  The ``ceph-crash`` script is normally run by systemd every 10 minutes to scrape any new reports and send them to the monitor/manager.  (See ``ceph crash -h`` for what these look like.)\r\n\r\nWhen deploying with rook, there is no systemd, and these crash reports are lost inside the individual daemon pods.\r\n\r\n1. Bind the host ``/var/lib/ceph/$cluster_namespace/crash`` to the container ``/var/lib/ceph/crash``.\r\n2. Rook should run ``ceph-crash -p /var/lib/ceph/$cluster_namespace/crash`` on every host where Rook's Ceph cluster has/had daemons running on a periodic basis.  (Every 10 minutes still sounds like a reasonable default to me.)",
